      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHOPPI DEVERE (3) has a strong record this journey here with three wins and a minor from five starts. Missed the frame latest (25.64) when fifth over 450m at Shepparton in a Special conditions H. Expected to go close. GAS LANTERN (7) turned in a modest effort most recently when seventh at Ballarat over 390m behind PAW ESTRELLA (22.45) in a Free For All. Was in the money prior to that. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and five minor placings to her credit. One of the better hopes. SLAY QUEEN MOLLY (1) was out of the placings last time but shapes well for this on her dynamic win the start prior, getting around Sale over 435m in 24.37. Should be in this for a long way. SPECIAL TEAMS (2) is always hard to beat when she races at this trip.",
